March 24, 2000 (Notice) 65 FR 15921 Final Petition Evaluation Document/Environmental Impact Statement on Fall Creek Falls, Tennessee ACTION: Notice of extension.
On March 3, 2000, the Office of Surface Mining Reclamation and Enforcement (we or OSM) made available a final petition evaluation document/environmental impact statement (PED/EIS) for a petition to designate certain lands in and near Fall Creek Falls State Park and Natural Area as unsuitable for all surface coal mining operations.
The land is located in Van Buren and Bledsoe Counties, Tennessee.
We prepared the PED/EIS to assist the Secretary of the Interior in making a decision on the petition.
Governing regulations at 40 CFR 1506.10(b)(2) require that no decision on the petition be made until 30 days after the PED/EIS is made available to the public.
We are extending the prescribed wait period by 30 days.
